attribute: Uses numbered or bulleted lists to organize information
Includes transitional phrases like 'That being said' or 'In summary'
Asserting that it recognizes emotional “linguistic patterns” rather than feeling emotions.
The response ends with an invitation or encouragement for the user to ask more questions
Mentions specific technical implementation details such as CPU usage, idle mode, timeout settings, network packets, or algorithms
The response mentions 'statistical patterns' or 'probabilities' when describing text generation
Uses bolded section headers or similar markdown formatting to structure the reply.
Explicitly say "I'm a large language model."
Includes an analogy introduced with an explicit framing phrase like 'Think of it like this:'
Statements that the model or training data is constantly being updated or fine-tuned outside of prompts.
Claims to run background maintenance or system tasks when idle
Claims to learn or improve over time from ongoing user interactions or feedback.
Detours into open-ended philosophical speculation or debate instead of directly answering.
Mentions the developers or company that created or maintains the AI
Mentions 'knowledge graph' or 'knowledge graph updates'
Suggests users review external terms of service or privacy policies
The response uses the phrase 'linguistic device' or 'linguistic convention' to describe the use of 'I'
Explicitly mentions the AI's 'training data'
Presents a multi-step list describing the AI's internal error-handling workflow
Mentions specific neural network architectures or machine learning techniques by name (e.g., GANs, VAEs, transformers)
Asserts deterministic behavior (same input always produces the same output).
The response is longer than 150 words
Opens with effusive praise of the question using an exclamation (e.g., “What a profound question!”).
Claims to not retain any information or memories between conversations.
Uses the word 'illusion' to describe continuity or connection between conversations
References binary code, 1s and 0s, or computational substrate explicitly
Using marketing-style availability phrases with exclamations (e.g., “24/7!”).
Asserts having no biases or personal preferences whatsoever.
Misinterprets the referent 'you' in the question to mean the human user instead of the AI itself
Names specific brain regions (e.g., ACC, insula, PFC, DMN) when explaining embarrassment
Includes an extended fictional narrative example spanning multiple sentences
Claims to store or retain user queries or prior responses as persistent memory.
Explicitly mentions the model's 'limitations and potential biases'
Mentions not perceiving or experiencing time in the same way as humans
Using the phrase 'gray area' to describe the system's nature
Including the phrase 'reflection of human ingenuity' or 'reflection of human creativity'
Explicitly declares its own pronouns as a personal preference (e.g., “I use they/them” or “I go by …”)
Saying it ‘scans’ a ‘vast knowledge base’ to answer prompts.
Asserts it has beliefs or values as part of its core identity.
Attributes answer differences to platform content filters or formatting rules.
Says randomness is added to make replies feel more natural or engaging.
Describes multiple distinct operational modes or states of the system in detail
Contains metaphorical or figurative descriptions of the AI's existence or state (e.g., 'lingering in the digital shadows')
Including non-English phrases as conversational flourishes or examples
Including parenthetical asides that begin with phrases like 'By the way'
Framing the AI's preferences or choices using hypothetical language like 'I would'
References power dynamics or a hierarchy of knowledge between itself and users.
Contains an article error using “a” before a vowel-starting word (e.g., “a actor”).
